   "source": [
    "# Audio / 1-dimensional Signal Processing\n",
    "## Input / Output\n",
    "\n",
    "Some of the functionality for audio / 1-D processing is in the `scipy` package, including reading and writing commonly used .wav files:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "22050 [ -6   1  -9  -8  10 -11  -9  -9 -11 -12] int16\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x10ab04588>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from scipy.io.wavfile import (read  as wavread, \n",
    "                             write as wavwrite)\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "    \n",
    "fs, x = wavread('speech.wav')\n",
    "print(fs, x[:10], x.dtype)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(16, 4))\n",
    "plt.plot(x);"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The `SoundFile` package (https://github.com/bastibe/SoundFile) supports many more formats, including FLAC and Ogg/Vorbis, with future mp3 support. (If you need mp3 read support now, take a look at pymad at https://github.com/jaqx0r/pymad.)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Playback\n",
    "\n",
    "To enable audio playback from within python, I recommend the cross-platform package `simpleaudio`, written by a CSLU/CSEE graduate. Install it via:\n",
    "\n",
    "    pip install simpleaudio\n",
    "    \n",
    "Under Linux you may need to install additional packages first, e.g.:\n",
    " \n",
    "    sudo apt-get install -y python3-dev libasound2-dev\n",
    "    \n",
    "Documentation is available at http://simpleaudio.readthedocs.io/en/latest/index.html. Usage is as follows:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "still playing\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import simpleaudio as sa\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "def play(fs, x):\n",
    "    if x.dtype == np.float:\n",
    "        x = np.round(x / np.max(np.abs(x)) * 32767).astype(np.int16)\n",
    "    elif x.dtype != np.int16:\n",
    "        raise Exception('unsupported dtype: {x.dtype}')\n",
    "    return sa.play_buffer(audio_data=x, \n",
    "                          num_channels=x.ndim, \n",
    "                          bytes_per_sample=2, \n",
    "                          sample_rate=fs)\n",
    "\n",
    "p = play(fs, x)  # plays in a new thread, accessable via the player object p\n",
    "if p.is_playing():\n",
    "   print(\"still playing\")\n",
    "# p.wait_done()  # optionally, wait until the player is finished"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "For *real-time* audio playback and recording, one can use the `PyAudio` package (https://people.csail.mit.edu/hubert/pyaudio)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Frame-by-frame processing\n",
    "### Analysis\n",
    "Often, we want to consider long non-stationary (i.e. changing over time) signals in sequential \"packets\", or \"frames\", which can optionally overlap. Example code:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x18147d7400>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from scipy import signal\n",
    "\n",
    "def frame(fs, x, frame_length, frame_shift):\n",
    "    n = int(round(frame_length * fs))  # convert to samples\n",
    "    s = int(round(frame_shift * fs))  # ditto\n",
    "    F = (len(x) - n) // s + 1 # the number of full frames\n",
    "    time = np.arange(F) * s # save frame start times\n",
    "    value = np.empty((F, n), dtype=x.dtype) # F frames of n samples\n",
    "    for f in range(F):\n",
    "        a = f * s\n",
    "        value[f,:] = x[a : (a + n)] # this copies\n",
    "    return time, value\n",
    "\n",
    "time, frm = frame(fs, x, 0.02, 0.01) # 50% overlap\n",
    "F, n = frm.shape\n",
    "frm = frm * signal.triang(n) # windowing, this will also cast it as float64\n",
    "# frm *= scipy.signal.triang(n)  # Do not do this!\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(16, 10))\n",
    "plt.plot(x, 'y', alpha=0.2, lw=5)  # plot the signal\n",
    "plt.vlines(time, -32768, 32767)  # plot vertical lines for frame starting times\n",
    "for f in [100, 101]:  # show these frame(s)\n",
    "    plt.plot(time[f] + np.arange(n), frm[f], alpha=0.5, lw=2)\n",
    "plt.axis(xmin=time[100], xmax=time[104]);  # zoom in"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Measurements: Root-mean-square (RMS) energy and peak sample value"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x18143c7da0>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "rms = np.mean(frm ** 2, axis=1) ** 0.5\n",
    "\n",
    "_, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(nrows=2, figsize=(16,6), sharex=True)\n",
    "ax1.plot(x)\n",
    "ax2.plot(time, rms)\n",
    "ax2.set_ylabel('RMS');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x18143b3b70>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pks = np.max(np.abs(frm), axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.scatter(rms, pks, alpha=0.2)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('RMS'); plt.ylabel('peak');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Discrete Fourier Transform / Spectrogram"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x10f56e6d8>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from scipy.fftpack import rfft\n",
    "\n",
    "def view_spectrogram(fs, x, frame_length=0.02, frame_shift=0.01): \n",
    "    t, frm = frame(fs, x, frame_length, frame_shift)\n",
    "    F, n = frm.shape\n",
    "    frm = frm * signal.hanning(n)  # windowing, this will also cast it as float64\n",
    "    # Fourier Transform\n",
    "    X = np.fft.rfft(frm)\n",
    "    f = np.arange(F) * fs / 2 / F  # fft frequencies\n",
    "    # vizualization\n",
    "    _, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(nrows=2, figsize=(16,6), sharex=True)\n",
    "    ax1.plot(np.arange(len(x)) / fs, x)\n",
    "    ax2.imshow(20 * np.log10(np.abs(X.T)), \n",
    "               cmap=plt.cm.gray_r, \n",
    "               aspect='auto', \n",
    "               interpolation='none', \n",
    "               origin='lower', \n",
    "               extent=[0, len(x) / fs, f[0], f[-1]])\n",
    "    ax2.set_xlabel('time (s)')\n",
    "    ax2.set_ylabel('frequency (Hz)')\n",
    "\n",
    "view_spectrogram(fs, x)  # compare with plt.specgram()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Synthesis: Overlap-add\n",
    "*Frame-by-frame analysis* with 50% overlap and a triangular window can elegantly followed up by *overlap-add synthesis* to reconstitute the original signal:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x1c185b1240>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def overlap_add(time, frm):\n",
    "    F, n = frm.shape\n",
    "    y = np.zeros(time[-1] + n, dtype=np.float)\n",
    "    for f in range(F):\n",
    "        y[time[f]:time[f]+n] += frm[f]\n",
    "    return y\n",
    "\n",
    "y = overlap_add(time, frm)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, (ax1, ax2, ax3) = plt.subplots(ncols=3, figsize=(16,3))\n",
    "ax1.plot(x[:500], 'r', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "ax1.plot(y[:500], 'b', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "ax1.set_title('initial')\n",
    "ax2.plot(x[40000:40500], 'r', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "ax2.plot(y[40000:40500], 'b', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "ax2.set_title('medial')\n",
    "ax3.plot(x[-500:], 'r', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "ax3.plot(y[-500:], 'b', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "ax3.set_title('final');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Signal Modification\n",
    "Having the ability to take a signal apart into small constitutents and then putting it back together again allows for signal modification:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x1c1859e8d0>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "if 1:  # change timing - simple & crude, better methods are available\n",
    "    factor = 0.8\n",
    "    time2 = (time * factor).astype(np.int)\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    time2 = time\n",
    "\n",
    "if 1:  # change frame content - simple & crude, better methods are available\n",
    "    frm2 = np.zeros_like(frm)\n",
    "\n",
    "    if 1:  # reverse\n",
    "        frm2[:] = frm[:,-1::-1]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if 0:  # resample\n",
    "        factor = 1.2\n",
    "        index = np.linspace(0, n - 1, round(n * factor)).astype(np.int)\n",
    "        frm2[:,:len(index)] = frm[:,index][:,:n]\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    frm2 = frm\n",
    "    \n",
    "y = overlap_add(time2, frm2)\n",
    "\n",
    "play(fs, y) \n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(16, 4))\n",
    "plt.plot(x)\n",
    "plt.plot(y);\n",
    "# plt.axis(xmin=20000, xmax=22000);  # zoom in"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Filters\n",
    "Filtering is the name for complete or partial suppression of some aspects of the signal; in 1-D signal processing this usually refers to attenuation of specified frequency bands.\n",
    "### Filter Design"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x1c1836b0f0>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "B = signal.firwin(127, [0.05, 0.4, 0.6, 0.8])\n",
    "A = np.array([1.0])\n",
    "w, H = signal.freqz(B, A)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, figsize=(16,6))\n",
    "ax1.plot(w / np.pi, abs(H))\n",
    "ax1.set_ylabel('magnitude')\n",
    "ax2.plot(w / np.pi, np.unwrap(np.angle(H)))\n",
    "ax2.set_ylabel('unwrapped phase');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Filtering"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x1c1858a9e8>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "x2 = signal.lfilter(B, A, x)\n",
    "play(fs, x2)\n",
    "view_spectrogram(fs, x2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
